       Numeric arguments to macros are  denoted  with  lowercase  letters  and
       string  arguments with uppercase.  An optional macro argument such as _x
       appears in brackets, [[_x]].  Note that arguments to macros generally must
       be  quoted if they contain whitespace.  An exception is the argument to
       header and footer macros, which require some  explanation.   They  take
       the  form "_c _l_e_f_t _c _m_i_d_d_l_e _c _r_i_g_h_t _c", with spaces added here for clar-
       ity.  The strings _l_e_f_t, _m_i_d_d_l_e, and  _r_i_g_h_t  correspond  to  their  page
       placement  and can contain unprotected whitespace, but must not contain
       the (non-space) character _c, which delimits them.  For brevity, the ta-
       ble  presents  header and footer arguments as _c_l_c_m_c_r_c.  Popular choices
       for _c are the ASCII apostrophe "''" and the ASCII double quote """".

